cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use EvalSurfer in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "EvalSurfer: A skill-first, agent-native evaluation protocol for AI applications"
abstract: >-
  EvalSurfer is a skill-first, agent-native evaluation protocol for AI
  applications. A portable SKILL.md routes the coding agent already running the
  session to act as the judge, while a deterministic, zero-dependency Python
  package — exposed as an MCP server of 48 tools the agent calls — plans scope,
  validates reports, auto-scores operational SLOs, explains failures, tracks
  regressions, calibrates judges, and gates releases. Unlike frameworks that own
  the judge model call, EvalSurfer makes no LLM API calls: the harness agent
  judges, the tools only measure.
